<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1554">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/629.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Garrett</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-09">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your July 2. Unless requested by the Spanish Embassy in this city to
                                take action regarding the reported theft from José Pereda, the
                                Department would not be justified in taking such action.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>